        <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm"><strong>What charger safety standards matter in 2026?</strong> IEC 62368-1 Edition 3 is now enforced globally. UL 62368-1 4th Edition (published July 2025) becomes mandatory February 15, 2027. China's GB 47372-2026 adds nail-penetration testing for power banks under CCC. For US retail, you need UL 62368-1 + FCC Part 15B. For EU, EN 62368-1 + EMC Directive. Power banks add UL 2056 and UN38.3. WOWOHCOOL holds all certifications and runs 8-hour 100% burn-in on every unit.</p>
