    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">4. 10-Layer Protection Circuit Map</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Every certified charger contains a chain of protection layers, each addressing a specific failure mode. This is the full signal path — from wall outlet to your device — with the named components that guard each stage.</p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-slate-200 rounded-xl">
        <thead class="bg-brandBlue text-white">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-center p-3 font-black uppercase text-xs">Stage</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 font-black uppercase text-xs">Protection Layer</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 font-black uppercase text-xs">Key Component</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 font-black uppercase text-xs">Failure Mode Addressed</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 font-black uppercase text-xs">Regulatory Reference</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="bg-white">
